pullRequest.body:
Proves that the (product) sum of a list mapped through a function of the form `if x = a then ... else ...` is equal to the (product) sum over the list mapped through the else condition, (times) plus an additional factor about the number of times `a` appears.

Upstreamed from [another project](https://github.com/BoltonBailey/formal-snarks-project).

Did you mean
```suggestion
lemma prod_map_ite_eq {A : Type*} [DecidableEq A] (l : List A) (f g : A â†’ G) (a : A) :
```
Please clarify. Why haven't you? If it doesn't work, is there a reason to assume it will work in the future?
It requires a version of `abel` for multiplicative groups rather than additive ones, as is being worked on #13233 (and I guess also #13442), I'll clarify this.
Actually, seems `abel` itself is not supposed to be imported in this file at all, so I'll just remove the comment.
(and use the golf technique from [here](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Dependencies.20of.20abel))

```suggestion
    (l.map fun x => if x = a then f x else g x).prod = (f a / g a) ^ (l.count a) * (l.map g).prod := by
```
